title: Kentucky-Florida renew GameDay rivalry
text:
Kentucky and Florida will renew its SEC rivalry Saturday night when the No. 6 Wildcats (18-4, 8-1 SEC) tangle with the No. 23 Gators (17-5, 7-2) in Gainesville. 
But Kentucky and Florida also have quite the ESPN College GameDay rivalry going. 
Get the latest UK news sent straight to your inbox with out EMAIL NEWSLETTER 
The Wildcats and Gators will meet for the seventh time for GameDay, second only to Duke and North Carolina's eight matchups, with Florida holding a 5-1 advantage. 
This will mark the fifth time Florida has hosted College GameDay, all of which have come when Kentucky has been in town, including two of the Wildcats' last three trips to Gainesville. 
Kentucky is making its second consecutive appearance on ESPN's College GameDay and 14th overall, with the Wildcats posting a 5-8 record in those games.
